sub_title: MSc Urban Management and Development (Urban Economic Development) at IHS, Erasmus University Rotterdam
summary:
Multilingual professional with a master in Development Studies and Public Policy (MA) and in Urban Management and Development (MSc) I have relevant work experience within institutions promoting development in the public sector, private sector and international cooperation. I have worked as a consultant, public servant in coordination and managerial positions. 

Significant experience in the formulation, implementation and evaluation of social projects and public policies, I have the ability to perform as an official with leadership and responsibility. From an experience in national and international institutions, I have the ability to adapt to different scenarios and working conditions, with the challenges that this imply. I have worked on different topics such as health, education, culture, security and economic development. I also have practical experience in innovation and entrepreneurship.

In addition, I have kept constant contact with academy since I have worked for two years as visiting university professor of Political Economy and Qualitative Methods.
